---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="Scrabble Words With Only Consonants — CWM, CRWTH, NTH, SHH, HMM, BRR, TSK" description="Consonant-only Scrabble words: CWM (10pts), CRWTH (13pts), NTH (6pts), SHH (9pts), HMM (10pts), BRR (5pts), TSK (7pts). Emergency plays for vowel-less racks." keywords="scrabble consonant only words, cwm scrabble, crwth scrabble, no vowel words scrabble, consonant words valid, shh hmm brr tsk scrabble">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words With Only Consonants — CWM, CRWTH, NTH, SHH, HMM, BRR, TSK","description":"Emergency consonant-only Scrabble words: CWM, CRWTH, NTH, SHH, HMM, BRR, TSK for when you draw no vowels.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-only-consonants"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What Scrabble words have no vowels?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Valid vowel-less words include CWM (10pts, a geological basin), CRWTH (13pts, a Welsh string instrument), NTH (6pts, to the nth degree), SHH (9pts, be quiet), HMM (10pts, expressing thought), BRR (5pts, cold), and TSK (7pts, disapproval sound)."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Are CWM and CRWTH really valid Scrabble words?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes — both are valid in SOWPODS and TWL dictionaries. CWM is a geological term for a cirque (steep-sided hollow), borrowed from Welsh. CRWTH is a Welsh bowed string instrument. Both use W as a vowel sound in Welsh, making them legal consonant-only plays."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"When should you play consonant-only words?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Play them when your rack has no vowels and exchanging isn't strategic (late game, close score, bag nearly empty). CWM and CRWTH score well for their length. SHH, HMM, and TSK are useful for tight board spots where short words fit."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words With Only Consonants — Emergency Plays</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Drawing a rack of all consonants feels hopeless — but it doesn't have to be. Scrabble has a small set of legal words that contain zero vowels. CWM and CRWTH borrow from Welsh (where W acts as a vowel), while SHH, HMM, BRR, and TSK are interjections that score surprisingly well for their size. Memorise these seven words and you'll never be stuck with a consonant-heavy rack again.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">7</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Vowelless Words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">13</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Top Score (CRWTH)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">0</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Vowels Required</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2-5</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letter Range</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">All Consonant-Only Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 CRWTH</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 points · 5 letters · C(3)+R(1)+W(4)+T(1)+H(4) · Welsh instrument</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 CWM</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 points · 3 letters · C(3)+W(4)+M(3) · Geological basin</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ HMM</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 points · 3 letters · H(4)+M(3)+M(3) · Thinking sound</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ SHH</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 points · 3 letters · S(1)+H(4)+H(4) · Be quiet</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800/40"><p class="text-white font-semibold text-sm mb-1">TSK</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">7 points · 3 letters · T(1)+S(1)+K(5) · Disapproval</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800/40"><p class="text-white font-semibold text-sm mb-1">NTH</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">6 points · 3 letters · N(1)+T(1)+H(4) · To the nth degree</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800/40"><p class="text-white font-semibold text-sm mb-1">BRR</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">5 points · 3 letters · B(3)+R(1)+R(1) · Cold expression</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800/40"><p class="text-white font-semibold text-sm mb-1">TSKTSKS</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">15 points · 7 letters · Plural/verb form · Bingo eligible!</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">When to Use These Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Late-game emergency:</span> When the bag is nearly empty and you can't exchange, these words save you from passing. CWM and CRWTH score 10-13 points — better than zero from a pass.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Tight board spots:</span> SHH, HMM, NTH, and TSK are 3 letters — they fit in cramped positions where longer words can't go. On premium squares, SHH on a DWS = 18 points from three letters.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Dump consonants strategically:</span> Playing CWM dumps C, W, M — making room for vowels on your next draw. This is rack management: score points while improving your leave.</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CRWTH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CWM</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">HMM</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SHH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TSK</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">NTH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BRR</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Memorise just <span class="text-white font-medium">7 words</span> and you'll never be helpless with a vowelless rack. CWM and CRWTH are especially valuable — they score 10-13 points while clearing consonants to improve your next draw.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-with-no-vowels/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words With No Vowels</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/consonant-heavy-rack-strategy/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Consonant-Heavy Rack Strategy</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/dealing-with-bad-tiles/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Dealing With Bad Tiles</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Stuck with consonants? Enter your tiles and find every valid play — free, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
